      div.card
        img(src="static/bulimba.webp" alt="A photo of rectification works on a damaged pipe")
        div-project-content
          div.header-and-tag
            h3 Damaged Pipe Dispute
            div.tag Bulimba
          h5.brand The problem
          p.large.grey-text A client couldn’t start building because a demolition contractor damaged a sewer line. They were stuck: no building approval until it was fixed, no clear advice on how to proceed, and their builder threatening delays.
          h5.brand What we did
          p.large.grey-text We stepped in, assessed the damage, advised on dispute resolution, designed the rectification, and worked directly with council to get approvals sorted. Then we supervised the repair to make sure it was done right.
          h5.brand The outcome
          p.large.grey-text Approval granted, delay avoided, and the client moved ahead with confidence.
      div.card
        div-project-content
          div.header-and-tag
            h3 Sewer Works in Congested Services
            div.tag Chermside
          h5.brand The problem
          p.large.grey-text A contractor was faced with a non-compliant design, service clashes underground, and tight staging requirements. To make it worse, a cyclone event hit mid- works, putting the project at risk.
          h5.brand What we did
          p.large.grey-text We advised on design changes, developed a practical staging plan, and designed a custom sewer bypass to keep works going. When the cyclone hit, we helped the team manage the emergency response.
          h5.brand The outcome
          p.large.grey-text The works stayed on track despite the setbacks, and the contractor avoided major delays and cost blowouts.
        img(src="static/chermside.webp" alt="A photo of sewer works")
      div.card
        img(src="static/mine.webp" alt="A photo of a road construction at a mine")
        div-project-content
          div.header-and-tag
            h3 Remote Haul Road Feasibility
            div.tag Private Mine Client
          h5.brand The problem
          p.large.grey-text A mine operator needed a 26 km haul road to move coal but had no in-house capability to assess the options or costs.
          h5.brand What we did
          p.large.grey-text We analysed transport alternatives, produced a high-level design, and prepared a Class 5 cost estimate that could be used in planning and procurement.
          h5.brand The outcome
          p.large.grey-text The client gained the clarity to move to the next phase of project planning, with realistic costs and a clear strategy.

